Jefferies Hires Six Heads of Equity Sales, Trading in Hong Kong

-- B y   L y n n   T h o m a s s o n
-- 
2011-04-11T05:16:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/jefferies-hires-six-heads-of-equity-sales-trading-in-hong-kong.html
Jefferies Group Inc. (JEF) , a New York-
based investment bank, said it added six people in Hong Kong to
boost its Asian equity sales and trading business.  The company hired Paul Krake as head of hedge-fund sales,
Lydia Leung for Hong Kong and China equity sales and Stephen
Nichols to oversee Asian trading, according to a press release.
Adam Putterill was picked as head of sales trading in Hong Kong
and China, James Young joined as head of regional sales and
 David Welch  was named as a regional sales trader, the statement
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lynn Thomasson in Hong Kong at 
 lthomasson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 